### Basic Syntax

```html
<div 
  data-user-id="1456"
  data-role="admin"
  data-is-active="true"
  data-price="49.99"
  data-product-name="Wireless Headphones">
  Content here...
</div>
```

**Rules:**
- Hamesha `data-` se shuru hona chahiye
- Dashes (`-`) allowed hain (kebab-case best practice)
- Values strings hote hain (numbers, booleans bhi string ke roop mein save hote hain)

### 1. JavaScript Mein Access Karna (Sabse Common)

```js
const card = document.querySelector('.card');

// Get value
console.log(card.dataset.userId);        // "1456"
console.log(card.dataset.role);          // "admin"
console.log(card.dataset.isActive);      // "true" (string)
console.log(card.dataset.price);         // "49.99"

// Set value
card.dataset.status = "verified";

// Remove attribute
delete card.dataset.price;
```

**Note:** 
- `dataset` object camelCase mein convert karta hai (`data-user-id` → `userId`)
- Values **hamesha string** mein milte hain

### 2. CSS Mein Use Karna (Very Powerful)

```css
/* Style based on data attribute */
div[data-role="admin"] {
  border-left: 5px solid #0066ff;
  background: #f0f8ff;
}

/* Using attribute selector */
[data-is-active="true"] {
  opacity: 1;
}

[data-is-active="false"] {
  opacity: 0.6;
  filter: grayscale(80%);
}
```

### 3. Real-World Practical Examples

**Example 1: Delete Confirmation Button**

```html
<button 
  data-action="delete"
  data-id="789"
  data-name="Project Alpha">
  Delete
</button>
```

```js
document.querySelectorAll('button[data-action="delete"]').forEach(btn => {
  btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const id = btn.dataset.id;
    const name = btn.dataset.name;
    
    if (confirm(`Delete ${name}?`)) {
      deleteItem(id);
    }
  });
});
```

**Example 2: Theme Switcher**

```html
<div data-theme="dark">...</div>
```

```css
[data-theme="dark"]  { background: #1e2937; color: white; }
[data-theme="light"] { background: white; color: #1e2937; }
```

### 4. Best Practices

- **Semantic** naam rakho: `data-user-id`, `data-product-price`, `data-status`
- BoHot saare data attributes mat daalo (performance impact pad sakta hai)
- `dataset` object use karo instead of `getAttribute()`
- Numbers aur booleans ko JavaScript mein properly convert karo:

```js
const price = parseFloat(card.dataset.price);
const isActive = card.dataset.isActive === "true";
```

### 5. When to Use `data-*` Attributes?

**Use Karo Jab:**
- Extra metadata store karna ho (ID, status, price, type)
- JavaScript ko configuration deni ho
- CSS ke through conditional styling chahiye
- Custom components banana ho (tabs, accordions, modals)

**Avoid Karo Jab:**
- Styling ke liye (classes ya CSS variables better hain)
- Sensitive / secret data store karna ho (security risk)